\section{Definition}
\label{sec:org5d3be45}

Given manifolds \(X,Y\) the \(r^{th}-\text{order}\) Jet space
 \(J^r(X,Y)\) is defined as the equivalence classes of
triples \((x,U,f)\) where
\begin{itemize}
\item \(x\in U\subset X\)
\item and \(f:U\to Y\)
\end{itemize}
such that where \((x,U,f)\sim (y,V,g)\) if
\(x=y\), \(f(x)=g(x)\) and the derivatives of
\(f|_{U\cap V}\) and \(g|_{U\cap V}\) agree at \(x\) up to order \(r\)
(in some i.e. any chart).

And equivalence class in \(J^r(X,Y)\) is called
an \emph{\(r\) -jet from \(X\) to \(Y\)}.

We also define sets \(J^r(X,Y)_y\) and
\({}_{x}J^r(X,Y)\)  as the \(r\) -jets such that
\((x_0,U,f)\) such that \(f(x_0)=y\) in the first case
and \(x_0=x\) in the second case.


\section{examples}
\label{sec:orge2aeb77}

\({}_0J^1(\mathbb{R},Y) = TY\)
\(J^1(X,\mathbb{R})_0 = T^*X\)
